	Commitments and Contingencies







	From time to time, the Company has been, is or may in the future be a defendant in various legal actions arising in the normal
	course of business. The Company records a provision for a liability when it is both probable that a liability has been incurred and the amount of loss can be reasonably estimated.


	The Company is not a party to any litigation that could reasonably be foreseen to be material to the Company.


	 






